Third-Party Components and Attributions
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PeakVox is a model-agnostic Universal Voice Runtime. It integrates and depends
on software developed by third parties — including multiple speech model
runtimes. Their licenses govern your use of those components and are not
modified by the PeakVox Community License. PeakVox orchestrates these runtimes;
it is an independent project and is not affiliated with or endorsed by their
respective teams.

1. Model runtimes (interchangeable providers)

   a. OmniVoice (k2-fsa/OmniVoice) — the first integrated provider
      - Source:  https://github.com/k2-fsa/OmniVoice
      - Model:   https://huggingface.co/k2-fsa/OmniVoice
      - License: Apache License 2.0
      - A massively-multilingual zero-shot text-to-speech and voice-cloning
        engine. Where required by the Apache License 2.0, this NOTICE preserves
        the relevant attribution and must be retained in redistributions.

   b. F5-TTS — integrated runtime
      - License and attribution per its upstream project; retained per that
        project's terms.

   c. Kokoro — integrated runtime (CPU-capable)
      - Distributed via the `kokoro` package; license and attribution per its
        upstream project, retained per that project's terms.

   Additional runtimes (e.g. Fish Audio, XTTS, OpenVoice, and future providers)
   integrate behind the same contract and are governed by their own upstream
   licenses. Each runtime you install retains its own license; consult that
   runtime's source and model card for the governing terms.

